\pard\f0\fs28    {\b 101. C. subsericans} Halácsy,{\i  Magyar Bot. Lapok}{\b  11}: 164 (1912). Perennial. Stems 10-35 cm, ascending, simple or with one short branch. Leaves appressed-white-tomentose; lower pinnatisect with segments 1-2 mm wide. Capitula solitary. Involucre 12-14 × 7 mm; appendages blackish, auriculate, with 2-3 fimbriae on each side and an apical spine 2-3 mm. Florets pink. Pappus c. 1/3 as long as achene.{\i  Mountain rocks. • S.E. Greece} ({\i Pateras Oros, near Megara}). Gr.
\par
