\pard\f0\fs28    {\b 102. C. attica} Nyman,{\i  Syll.} 33 (1854-1855) ({\i C. graeca} sensu Boiss. & Spruner, non Griseb.,{\i  C. boissieri} Walpers, non DC.). Perennial. Stems 5-30 cm, erect or ascending, usually branched below the middle. Leaves usually more or less whitish-tomentose, rarely glabrescent; lower 1(-2)-pinnatisect, the segments 1 mm wide or more; upper undivided. Capitula solitary. Involucre 10-16 × 5-10 mm; bracts with 3 veins; appendages with a long apical spine, sometimes auriculate. Florets pink or purple. Pappus 1/3 as long to as long as achene.{\i  Mountain rocks. • N. & E. Greece.} Gr.
