\pard\f0\fs28   {\b C. poculatoris} W. Greuter,{\i  Bauhinia}{\b  3}: 252 (1967), from crevices of calcareous rocks in W. Kriti (Aspéndos), has not been collected in flower or fruit but appears to be a distinct species related to {\b 102}; it is a perennial, with procumbent stems 5-10 cm, leaves white-floccose-tomentose at least beneath but more or less glabrescent, the basal sinuate-pinnatifid to pinnatisect with ovate to suborbicular segments and the upper subentire, solitary capitula with involucre 12-16 × 6-8 mm, and pectinate-ciliate appendages with a slender, erect apical spine.
\par
