\pard\f0\fs28    {\b 103. C. soskae} Hayek ex Kosanin,{\i  Glas Srpske Kralj. Akad.}{\b  119}: 275 (1926). Perennial. Stems erect, paniculately branched. Leaves whitish-tomentose; lower pinnatisect, with linear-lanceolate segments 1-2 mm wide. Capitula solitary. Involucre 15 × 8-10 mm, ovoid; appendages pale brown, auriculate, with more or less erect apical spine 3-4 mm. Florets yellow. Pappus about as long as achene.{\i  Rocky places. • S. & E. Jugoslavia.} Ju.
\par
\par
\pard\f0\fs28    {\b 104. C. kartschiana} Scop., {\i Fl. Carn.} ed. 2, {\b 2}: 140 (1772). Perennial. Stems 30-40 cm, erect, with long, paniculate branches. Leaves glabrous, scabrid; lower pinnate. Capitula solitary. Involucre 11 × 9 mm, ovoid-globose; appendages yellowish, with patent apical spine 1-1·5 mm, without auricles. Florets pink. Pappus as long as or longer than achene. •{\i  N.E. Italy, N.W. Jugoslavia}. It Ju.
\par
