\pard\f0\fs28   Sect. PANICULATAE (Hayek) Dostál. Stems herbaceous, often paniculately branched, the branches not spiny. Leaf-segments not rigid or spiny. Involucre usually ovoid; lower bracts usually without prominent veins on dorsal surface; appendages usually spiny, not filiform and plumose-fimbriate at apex, the lower fimbriae free, without auricles or hyaline margin. Florets purple, rarely pink or lilac.
\par
